Cihan News Agency Diary - Cihan

Cihan News Agency DiaryGMT 18:30Cihan News Agency latest on Thursday March 06, 2014Here are the main Video News items Cihan News Agency aims to cover today.TOP NEWSEXPECTED TURKEY-POLAND BUSINESS FORUM: President Abdullah Gül will attend closing session of the Turkey-Poland Business Forum and will 600th anniversary of Polish-Turkish Relations Exhibition. (17:00-19:00)ICC PRESIDENT PRESS CONFERENCE/TURKEY: International Chamber of Commerce Turkey National Committee CEO Rıfat Hisarcıklıoğlu will hold a press meeting with ICC President Harold McGraw at Turkish Union of Chambers and Commodity Exchanges (TOBB) building. (11:30)ÇAVUŞOĞLU/HITHITIT UNIVERSITY GROUNDBREAKING: EU Minister and Chief Negotiator Mevlüt Çavuşoğlu will attend groundbreaking ceremony of Hitit University Research and Training Hospital after visiting Çorum Governorship and Municipality. (14:45-17:00)DELIVEREDUKRAINIAN PM-NATO CHIEF: Ukrainian Prime Minister Arsenii Yatseniuk visited NATO headquarter at Brussels and attended a press conference with Secretary General Anders Fogh Rasmussen on Thursday. During his statements at the press-conference, Rasmussen underlined that NATO stands by Ukraine’s sovereignty and territorial integrity.XINJIANG GOVERNOR/TERRORISM: A top government official from far west China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region blamed the separatist activities in the ethnic area on overseas forces Thursday, saying that they will never achieve their purpose.TURKISH SOLDIER DIES: A Turkish soldier died following a land mine blast in the southeastern province of Şırnak on Thursday.OIC CONDEMNS ISRAEL: The Organization of Islamic Conference (OIC) condemned the attempt of the Israeli Parliament to enact laws aiming at imposing Israeli sovereignty over the holy Islamic sites in Jerusalem.CONSTITUTIONAL COURT/EX ARMY CHIEF: Turkish Constitutional Court has ruled that personal freedoms and security of former army chief İlker Başbuğ, who is a suspect in the Ergenekon investigation, were violated.SHIP BURNS IN ISTANBUL: A fire erupted on a ship off the İstanbul coast near Yenikapı port on Thursday afternoon. Firefighting ships are currently battling the fire and the cloud of smoke could be seen covering the Bosporus Strait. Helicopters have also been dispatched to drop water to help extinguish the fire.EXPEDITION 39/40 TRAINING: Expedition 39/40 Soyuz Commander Alexander Skvortsov of the Russian Federal Space Agency (Roscosmos), NASA Flight Engineer Steve Swanson and Flight Engineer Oleg Artemyev of Roscosmos conducted final qualification training at the Gagarin Cosmonaut Training Center in Star City, Russia March 4 and 5. The three are scheduled for a March 26 launch, Kazakh time, in the Soyuz TMA-12M spacecraft to begin a six-month mission on the International Space Station.SPACE STATION LIVE: Public Affairs Officer Lori Meggs at the Marshall Space Flight Center in Huntsville, Alabama spoke with NASA Jet Propulsion Laboratory scientists Anita Sengupta and Michael Hohensee about the Cold Atom Laboratory and how it could change what we know about fundamental physics.ARCHIBISHOPS CONVENE IN ISTANBUL: Patricians and archbishops from 14 Orthodox churches came to together at Aya Yorgi Greek Orthodox Church in Fener Greek Patriarchate for a three-day meeting upon the invitation of Fener Greek Patriarch Bartholomeos.SATELLITE REFUELING TEST: NASA's Goddard Space Flight Center in Maryland and Kennedy Space Center in Florida joined teams and efforts to test new robotic refueling technologies that could help satellites live longer in space.UN/SYRIAN CHEMICAL WEAPONS: Speaking today to the press at UN Headquarters in New York following her briefing to the Security Council on Wednesday, Sigrid Kaag, Special Coordinator of the UN-OPCW Joint Mission, said that "one third of the Syria's chemical weapons materials has been removed or destroyed."UGANDIAN OPINION LEADER PRAISES HIZMET: A prominent opinion leader in Uganda commented on a news report which was published by a pro-government daily, Yeni Şafak, which defames Turkish schools established by entrepreneurs affiliated with Hizmet Movement by quoting him.UN'S THREATENED ADVISOR: Deputy Secretary-General Jan Eliasson told reporters in New York that Senior Advisor Robert Serry is in good shape physically after being threatened on Wednesday (5 Mar) during his visit to Crimea, Ukraine, by armed men who ordered him to leave the region.NATO-RUSSIA RELATIONS: Western diplomats met in Europe Wednesday on the crisis in Ukraine as NATO warned it was reviewing its relationship with Russia.DINNER IN HONOR OF KOMOROWSKI: President Gül gave dinner in honor of Polish President Bronislaw Komorowski and his wife Anna Komorowski, during which both presidents gave messages of friendship between the two countries at the 600th anniversary of diplomatic relations between them.CIHAN - LIVE POSITIONSlug: TURKEY SYRIA BORDEREvent: Covering latest developments from the Turkish province of Hatay along the Turkey Syria border.Location 1: Hatay YayladagiLocation 2: Gaziantep- KilisCAIRO, EGYPT (Mobile & Studio): Cihan’s complete broadcasting and multi-camera studio with transport allows your firm to access developments in Cairo, the cultural capital of the Arab World.WASHINGTON: (Mobile & Studio): Cihan’s complete broadcasting and multi-camera studio with transport allows your firm to access developments in Washington, USA.FRANKFURT: (Mobile) Mobile access to one of Germany’s and Europe’s largest cities and points.PARIS-(Mobile & Studio): Cihan’s complete broadcasting and multi-camera studio with transport allows your firm to access developments in Paris.BEIRUT: (Mobile & Studio) Cihan’s complete broadcasting and multi-camera studio with transport allows your firm to access developments in Lebanon’s capital city of Beirut.ISTANBUL, TURKEY - (Mobile): Follow the world from the middle of the world. Programming and TV access to Istanbul, a leading world city in art, culture, industry, media and transport.ANKARA